ce:section.ce:para:
As shown in Fig. 2
                        , when excited at 315nm (Fig. 2a and b), the quenching efficiency of DECNDs linearly increased with the glucose concentrations from 0.1 to 30μM and the LOD was 0.05μM. When excited at 365nm (Fig. 2c and d), with the addition of glucose, the emission at 530nm gradually decreased and the emission at 410nm almost unchanged; the emission ratios (F410/F530) showed linear responses to glucose concentrations between 0.1–45μM with LOD 0.03μM. Moreover, comparing with other reported methods for glucose determination (Table 1
                        ), the LOD of this assay was much lower.
